                    <h2 class="mt-3 font-['Sora'] text-2xl font-bold">Deployment</h2>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-8 text-cyan-100/80">
                        Key considerations when deploying RichTextBox to production environments.
                    </p>

                    <div class="mt-6 space-y-3">
                        <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-4">
                            <h4 class="font-['Sora'] text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-300">Pre-deploy checklist</h4>
                            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm leading-6 text-cyan-100/80">
                                <li>&#10003; <code>RichTextBox.lic</code> is included in the publish output (content root)</li>
                                <li>&#10003; <code>wwwroot/uploads</code> directory exists and is writable by the app pool identity</li>
                                <li>&#10003; <code>app.UseStaticFiles()</code> is called before <code>app.MapRichTextBoxUploads()</code></li>
                                <li>&#10003; Maximum request body size is configured for large file uploads</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-4">
                            <h4 class="font-['Sora'] text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-300">IIS</h4>
                            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-cyan-100/80">
                                Install the ASP.NET Core Hosting Bundle. Set <code>maxAllowedContentLength</code> in <code>web.config</code> for large uploads. Ensure the app pool identity has write access to the uploads folder.
                            </p>
